TY  - JOUR
T1  - Why a Central Network Position Isn't Enough: The Role of Motivation and Ability for Knowledge Sharing in Employee Networks
AU  - Reinholt, Mia
AU  - Pedersen, Torben
AU  - Foss, Nicolai J.
Y1  - 2011/12/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2009.0007
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2009.0007
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1277
EP  - 1297
VL  - 54
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Contrasting views exist on how network characteristics predict knowledge sharing. Although large, open egocentric networks foster network positions that provide access to nonredundant knowledge, critics have noted that such networks impair knowledge sharing, because trust and reciprocity do not thrive in them. This problem may, however, be resolved by including motivation and ability to share knowledge as moderators of the association between network position and knowledge sharing. Our analysis of 705 employees in a consultancy shows that employees' knowledge acquisition and provision are highest when network centrality, autonomous motivation, and ability are all high, thus supporting the proposed three-way interaction.
AB  - Contrasting views exist on how network characteristics predict knowledge sharing. Although large, open egocentric networks foster network positions that provide access to nonredundant knowledge, critics have noted that such networks impair knowledge sharing, because trust and reciprocity do not thrive in them. This problem may, however, be resolved by including motivation and ability to share knowledge as moderators of the association between network position and knowledge sharing. Our analysis of 705 employees in a consultancy shows that employees' knowledge acquisition and provision are highest when network centrality, autonomous motivation, and ability are all high, thus supporting the proposed three-way interaction.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2009.0007
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amj.2009.0007
Y2  - 2026/04/24
